#. REF: nya171, sc38
msgctxt "mn1:171.1"
msgid "Tathāgatopi, bhikkhave, arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pathaviṃ pathavito abhijānāti; "
msgstr "The Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha directly knows earth as earth. "

msgctxt "mn1:171.2"
msgid "pathaviṃ pathavito abhiññāya pathaviṃ na maññati, pathaviyā na maññati, pathavito na maññati, pathaviṃ meti na maññati, pathaviṃ nābhinandati. "
msgstr "But he doesn’t identify with earth, he doesn’t identify regarding earth, he doesn’t identify as earth, he doesn’t identify that ‘earth is mine’, he doesn’t take pleasure in earth. "

msgctxt "mn1:171.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

#. VAR: Nandī → nandi (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "mn1:171.4"
msgid "‘Nandī dukkhassa mūlan’ti—"
msgstr "Because he has understood that relishing is the root of suffering, "

msgctxt "mn1:171.5"
msgid "iti viditvā ‘bhavā jāti bhūtassa jarāmaraṇan’ti. "
msgstr "and that rebirth comes from continued existence; whoever has come to be gets old and dies. "

msgctxt "mn1:171.6"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘tathāgato sabbaso taṇhānaṃ khayā virāgā nirodhā cāgā paṭinissaggā anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "That’s why the Realized One—with the ending, fading away, cessation, giving up, and letting go of all cravings—has awakened to the supreme perfect Awakening, I say. "

